#Text=Wikinews Shorts : January 27 , 2012
#Text=A compilation of brief news reports for
#Text=Friday , January 27 , 2012 .
#Text=If you believe any of these stories deserves more in-depth coverage , feel free to write a full article on the issues raised .
#Text=Medicins Sans Frontieres announces partial withdrawal over Libyan torture abuses
#Text=Medicins Sans Frontieres ( MSF ) have announced a partial withdrawal from Libya .
#Text=The medical charity announced they will no longer work at Libyan detention centres due to facing treating torture victims in order to make them well enough to be further tortured .

#Text=MSF General Director Christopher Stokes said : " Our role is to provide medical care to war casualties and sick detainees , not to repeatedly treat the same patients between torture sessions " .
#Text=The United Nations estimates that some 8,500 former Gaddafi loyalists are being held by a number of unregulated , and unaccountable , armed groups .
#Text=Damien McElroy .
#Text=" Libya : UN alarmed over failure to stop torture of detainees " — The Telegraph , January 26 , 2012
#Text=" Libyan detainees die after torture , says Amnesty International " — BBC News Online , January 26 , 2012
#Text=Jagger tells World Economic Forum , " ca n't always get what you want "
#Text=Lead singer of The Rolling Stones Mick Jagger has withdrawn from the ' Great British Tea Party ' in Davos , Switzerland .

#Text=Cutting short his visit to the 2012 World Economic Forum , as well as pulling out of Prime Minister David Cameron 's event intended to promote UK creativity , Jagger complained of both " being used as a political football " and " comment[s ] about my political allegiances which are inaccurate .

column1: #Text=UK Prime Minister calls for European Union to be more competetive
#Text=Speaking at the World Economic Forum in Davos , the UK Prime Minister David Cameron called on European Union leaders to be " bold " and " decisive " to boost growth and promote business .

#Text=Labelling a proposed financial transactions tax as " madness " he attacked " unnecessary " regulations on business , telling attendees that " Europe 's lack of competitiveness remains its Achilles heel .

#Text=Coup in Papua New Guinea fails
#Text=A military coup in Papua New Guinea failed with the capture of at least fifteen mutineers .

#Text=These supporters of deposed former Prime Minister Sir Michael Thomas Somare seized a military barracks , and the nation 's military head , early on Thursday morning and demanded Somare be reinstated .
#Text=The Supreme Court of Papua New Guinea previously ruled that Somare be reinstated , concluding that current Prime Minister Peter O'Neill was unlawfully appointed .
#Text=" Papua New Guinea PM Says Military Mutiny is Over " — Voice of America , January 26 , 2012
#Text=Kate Hodal .
#Text=" Papua New Guinea military coup fails " — The Guardian , January 26 , 2012
#Text=Australian Prime Minister rescued from protesters

#Text=During an Australia Day function , the country 's Prime Minister , Julia Gillard — and the leader of the opposition , Tony Abbott , had to be rescued after they were surrounded by as many as 200 aboriginal rights protesters at a Canberra restaurant .
#Text=The protesters , from the Aboriginal Tent Embassy , appear to have been angered by Abbot 's suggestion that it was time for the Embassy , now in its fortieth year , to come down .
#Text=" Julia Gillard ' rescued ' amid Australia Day protests " — BBC News Online , January 26 , 2012
#Text=" Australian PM stumbles before angry protesters " — CBS News , January 26 , 2012
